Interface ProxyRaw

public interface ProxyRaw
extends HasHandlers

This is the unparameterized base interface for proxy. It is provided as a work around since GIN/Guice cannot inject parameterized types. For most purposes you should use Proxy.

Author:
Philippe Beaudoin

Method Detail

getRawPresenter

void getRawPresenter(AsyncCallback<Presenter<?,?>> callback)
Get the associated Presenter. The presenter can only be obtained in an asynchronous manner to support code splitting when needed. To access the presenter, pass a callback.

The difference between this method and Proxy.getPresenter(com.google.gwt.user.client.rpc.AsyncCallback) is that the latter one gets the specific parameterised Presenter type.

Parameters:
callback - The callback in which the Presenter will be passed as a parameter.
